metadata.name: JullyCar #133
metadata.description:
We all dream of having a car or we have

Some of us even talk to our car

And some of us see our car like a cartoon character.

This collection is not only an NFT but also a match
If you win one of the cups, in addition to a Super Rare edition, there are also prizes for the owners in the Primary market, which you can find on our Twitter ( @Morixels )

The JullyCar is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 10 (168 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 124,582,993,920 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of the most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @ardavan_
Made in 2022

metadata.name: =DMT= #465
metadata.description:
The Spirit Molecule, an experience out of this world, available in this world.

What will you see when you take your =DMT=? I wish you a great trip.

Groups of color palettes, lines and bezier curves combine to create what sometimes looks like a sun, an eye, a flower, an explosion, a pair of wings or a combination of these.

I hope in the future Psychedelics will be accessible to people in controlled settings with professional care and support. 
The Ayahuasca ceremonies happening around the world are a good step in this direction.

Press 's' to save a 3000x3000 px PNG.

Created by UpOnlyFan in August 2022 with p5js.

@(=_=)- @brainspinky2014 ¬(=_=)7

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #28
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Stiches #7
metadata.description:
We all got some kind of stiches. Some try to hide them, some are wearing them with pride. Here are mine. Hope you enjoy them.

The piece is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Initial resolution is the screen resolution. Although the piece is supposed to look the same no matter the resolution, we all know this is not possible. But I think I made a good job at it.

The royalties goes to me (30%), @toxi(30%) and the minter(40%).


Keyboard shortcuts

- 2 : download png @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : download png @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution

metadata.name: life is a (beautiful) mess #21
metadata.description:
when carefully applied, chaos brings things to life.

'life is a (beautiful) mess' was created as i led a certain amount of chaos take control of an animated textile algorithm i'm developing. 
as soon as it happened i realized that it was a great representation of our lives. 
each line represents one of us and the patterns that appear repeatedly are the situations we live which make us move, feel and be in a certain way. 
the image created is the sum of our paths in this life, as they only make sense when we look at them as one.

---

i hope you find it pleasant to watch this animation, how it develops and grows during aprox 1'30"
there are pieces drawn with the 4 typical school pen colors: black, green, blue and red. also a multicolor and a rare dark mode features.


press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the animation
doubleclick the mouse to resume the animation

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Verse #44
metadata.description:
Your unique iteration of Verse.

The prettiest, the coolest, simply the best.

Well done.

Our skies in the next 30 years as temperatures are intensifying and we experience, in the present, unprecedent heat waves. 

Inspired in polaroid images. Each output represents an image, a collectible and a document of perpetual suns. 

Each image showcases a random date and time in the next 30 years.

Oftentimes we will see how the suns try to breach the borders of the polaroid. They seldom manage to completely invade the frame.

Press “s” to save a png image.
Press “h” to save a high resolution: 5500 x 3660 or 3660 x 5500 png frame.
